  "derivation_layer": {
    "source_latex": "% BEGIN TZP DERIVATION LAYER\n\\tzpsection{Derivation Layer}\n\\paragraph{Primary Equation.}\n\\begin{equation}\nP_{\\mathrm{null}}(v)\n=\n\\begin{cases}\nv, & g(v,w)=0\\ \\text{for all}\\ w\\in T_pM,\\\\\n0, & \\text{otherwise}.\n\\end{cases}\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Primary Derivation.}\nAt the TZP, the degenerate metric admits null directions.  \nA vector $v\\in T_pM$ belongs to the null space if it pairs to zero with every tangent vector $w$:\n\n\\begin{equation}\ng(v,w)=0\n\\qquad\n\\forall w\\in T_pM .\n\\end{equation}\n\nThe null projection operator preserves vectors satisfying this condition:\n\n\\begin{equation}\nP_{\\mathrm{null}}(v)=v .\n\\end{equation}\n\nVectors not satisfying the null condition are removed by the projection:\n\n\\begin{equation}\nP_{\\mathrm{null}}(v)=0 .\n\\end{equation}\n\nThus,\n\n\\begin{equation}\n\\boxed{\nP_{\\mathrm{null}}(v)\n=\n\\begin{cases}\nv, & g(v,w)=0\\ \\text{for all}\\ w\\in T_pM,\\\\\n0, & \\text{otherwise}.\n\\end{cases}\n}\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Interpretation.}\n$P_{\\mathrm{null}}$ extracts only those tangent directions annihilated by the degenerate TZP metric.\n% END TZP DERIVATION LAYER"
  },
